WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.258 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.258 --> 00:00:08.604 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:08.604 --> 00:00:34.450 align:middle line:90%


00:00:34.450 --> 00:00:37.330 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm going to talk to you
this evening on the subject

00:00:37.330 --> 00:00:38.760 align:middle line:90%
of the spectrum of love.

00:00:38.760 --> 00:00:45.290 align:middle line:90%


00:00:45.290 --> 00:00:52.280 align:middle line:84%
We know that from
time to time, there

00:00:52.280 --> 00:00:57.960 align:middle line:84%
arise among human
beings people who

00:00:57.960 --> 00:01:05.591 align:middle line:84%
seem to exude love as naturally
as the sun gives out heat.

00:01:05.591 --> 00:01:11.370 align:middle line:90%


00:01:11.370 --> 00:01:12.930 align:middle line:90%
We would like to be like that.

00:01:12.930 --> 00:01:15.640 align:middle line:90%


00:01:15.640 --> 00:01:21.150 align:middle line:84%
And by and large,
man's religions

00:01:21.150 --> 00:01:33.505 align:middle line:84%
are attempts to cultivate that
same power in ordinary people.

00:01:33.505 --> 00:01:45.630 align:middle line:90%


00:01:45.630 --> 00:01:49.230 align:middle line:84%
>> These words from esteemed
philosopher Alan Watts require

00:01:49.230 --> 00:01:52.530 align:middle line:84%
us to stop and critically
analyze the very nature of who

00:01:52.530 --> 00:01:56.330 align:middle line:84%
we are and what it
means to be human.

00:01:56.330 --> 00:01:59.070 align:middle line:84%
Recently, physicists at
CERN astonished the world

00:01:59.070 --> 00:02:01.500 align:middle line:84%
with their theories on
supersymmetry and the Higgs

00:02:01.500 --> 00:02:04.090 align:middle line:90%
boson, or God particle.

00:02:04.090 --> 00:02:06.060 align:middle line:84%
Theoretic physicists
and philosophers

00:02:06.060 --> 00:02:08.580 align:middle line:84%
have gone on to propose
that we are in fact living

00:02:08.580 --> 00:02:11.880 align:middle line:84%
in the matrix through the
simulation hypotheses, which

00:02:11.880 --> 00:02:14.970 align:middle line:84%
suggests that our future
selves are rerunning computer

00:02:14.970 --> 00:02:17.440 align:middle line:90%
simulations.

00:02:17.440 --> 00:02:19.150 align:middle line:84%
Eastern philosophy
from the Upanishads

00:02:19.150 --> 00:02:21.250 align:middle line:90%
claims Tat Tvam Asi--

00:02:21.250 --> 00:02:23.830 align:middle line:90%
you and the absolute are one.

00:02:23.830 --> 00:02:25.737 align:middle line:90%
What, then, is real?

00:02:25.737 --> 00:02:29.076 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:29.076 --> 00:02:35.280 align:middle line:90%


00:02:35.280 --> 00:02:39.390 align:middle line:10%
Not so long ago, I began to
ask myself this question.

00:02:39.390 --> 00:02:42.870 align:middle line:10%
I grew up in South Africa, a
land with a violent history,

00:02:42.870 --> 00:02:45.300 align:middle line:10%
filled with angry,
loving, confused,

00:02:45.300 --> 00:02:48.120 align:middle line:10%
and proud people dealing
with an uncertain future.

00:02:48.120 --> 00:02:51.150 align:middle line:90%


00:02:51.150 --> 00:02:54.240 align:middle line:84%
In 1994, this all
changed as Nelson Mandela

00:02:54.240 --> 00:02:56.975 align:middle line:84%
became our first democratically
elected president, freeing

00:02:56.975 --> 00:02:59.160 align:middle line:90%
our land and its people.

00:02:59.160 --> 00:03:01.920 align:middle line:84%
In the same year that our great
land obtained its freedom,

00:03:01.920 --> 00:03:04.190 align:middle line:84%
my own world was
turned upside down.

00:03:04.190 --> 00:03:07.620 align:middle line:84%
Both my grandfather and
father had made the decision

00:03:07.620 --> 00:03:11.350 align:middle line:84%
to end their own lives within
a few months of one another.

00:03:11.350 --> 00:03:13.740 align:middle line:84%
This loss and pain was
the catalyst that led me

00:03:13.740 --> 00:03:16.980 align:middle line:90%
down a road of self-discovery.

00:03:16.980 --> 00:03:20.100 align:middle line:84%
The more I ask the
question what is real,

00:03:20.100 --> 00:03:22.990 align:middle line:90%
the less I seem to know.

00:03:22.990 --> 00:03:26.850 align:middle line:84%
And this is where the
real story begins.

00:03:26.850 --> 00:03:28.680 align:middle line:84%
Living oceans apart
from New York,

00:03:28.680 --> 00:03:30.630 align:middle line:84%
I never imagined that
our destines would

00:03:30.630 --> 00:03:33.070 align:middle line:90%
be so inextricably linked.

00:03:33.070 --> 00:03:36.180 align:middle line:84%
But destiny, it seems,
knows no boundaries.

00:03:36.180 --> 00:03:38.940 align:middle line:84%
At about the same time in which
my country and countless others

00:03:38.940 --> 00:03:41.790 align:middle line:84%
around the world were
experiencing the joys and fears

00:03:41.790 --> 00:03:45.110 align:middle line:84%
of transformation, two
visionaries, Sharon Gannon

00:03:45.110 --> 00:03:48.750 align:middle line:84%
and David Life, were beginning
to inspire a world of change

00:03:48.750 --> 00:03:52.170 align:middle line:84%
in a quaint, artistic
haven in the East Village

00:03:52.170 --> 00:03:54.760 align:middle line:84%
on the corner of Avenue
B and East 10 Street

00:03:54.760 --> 00:03:56.350 align:middle line:90%
called The Life Cafe.

00:03:56.350 --> 00:03:59.272 align:middle line:90%


00:03:59.272 --> 00:04:02.681 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:02.681 --> 00:04:04.142 align:middle line:90%


00:04:04.142 --> 00:04:08.870 align:middle line:10%
>> The East Village in 1984-'85
was a very unique and special

00:04:08.870 --> 00:04:09.670 align:middle line:10%
time.

00:04:09.670 --> 00:04:11.740 align:middle line:10%
And I'm really glad
that I got to be

00:04:11.740 --> 00:04:13.660 align:middle line:10%
front and center in
an environment that

00:04:13.660 --> 00:04:15.460 align:middle line:10%
