00:04:22.960 --> 00:04:24.860 align:middle line:10%
anywhere else.

00:04:24.860 --> 00:04:26.980 align:middle line:84%
>> It was a very
bohemian neighborhood.

00:04:26.980 --> 00:04:28.560 align:middle line:84%
That was part of
the charm of it.

00:04:28.560 --> 00:04:32.860 align:middle line:84%
Sort of a renaissance
just evolved there.

00:04:32.860 --> 00:04:35.860 align:middle line:10%
>> And growing up on the
Lower East Side itself had

00:04:35.860 --> 00:04:41.380 align:middle line:10%
an interesting mix of kind of
extreme violence and poverty,

00:04:41.380 --> 00:04:44.120 align:middle line:10%
but on the other side, this
incredibly beautiful artistic

00:04:44.120 --> 00:04:44.920 align:middle line:10%
spirit.

00:04:44.920 --> 00:04:48.320 align:middle line:90%


00:04:48.320 --> 00:04:51.680 align:middle line:10%
>> There was a kind of spirit
in the air of people questioning

00:04:51.680 --> 00:04:55.100 align:middle line:10%
authority, finding
better ways of living,

00:04:55.100 --> 00:04:58.880 align:middle line:10%
with different ambitions,
different ideas about what it

00:04:58.880 --> 00:05:01.910 align:middle line:10%
would mean to be successful.

00:05:01.910 --> 00:05:03.620 align:middle line:10%
>> People that really
were impassioned,

00:05:03.620 --> 00:05:08.870 align:middle line:10%
that felt that they needed to
find a wholesome vehicle with

00:05:08.870 --> 00:05:11.600 align:middle line:10%
which to kind of express
the temperament of what was

00:05:11.600 --> 00:05:12.500 align:middle line:10%
happening in society.

00:05:12.500 --> 00:05:15.350 align:middle line:84%
>> An incredible
amount of drive,

00:05:15.350 --> 00:05:18.110 align:middle line:84%
but not in such a
traditional sense.

00:05:18.110 --> 00:05:20.840 align:middle line:10%
It had the drive
to express yourself

00:05:20.840 --> 00:05:22.790 align:middle line:10%
in a way that was both
meaningful to others

00:05:22.790 --> 00:05:24.332 align:middle line:10%
and helpful to others.

00:05:24.332 --> 00:05:27.664 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:27.664 --> 00:05:31.480 align:middle line:90%


00:05:31.480 --> 00:05:35.540 align:middle line:84%
>> I moved to the Lower
East Side in 1979 and opened

00:05:35.540 --> 00:05:37.880 align:middle line:90%
the Life Cafe about 1980.

00:05:37.880 --> 00:05:41.570 align:middle line:10%
I had no working capital.

00:05:41.570 --> 00:05:44.870 align:middle line:84%
I was in an abandoned,
rundown storefront.

00:05:44.870 --> 00:05:47.460 align:middle line:84%
The rent was free
because it was that bad.

00:05:47.460 --> 00:05:51.450 align:middle line:84%
>> He asked me what I was going
to do when I finished college.

00:05:51.450 --> 00:05:52.705 align:middle line:90%
I said, I don't know.

00:05:52.705 --> 00:05:54.830 align:middle line:84%
He said, well, do you want
to come out to New York?

00:05:54.830 --> 00:05:56.720 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to open
an art gallery.

00:05:56.720 --> 00:06:00.620 align:middle line:84%
>> I thought initially, I
would open a store that had

00:06:00.620 --> 00:06:04.160 align:middle line:84%
collectible furniture and
collectible items like Life

00:06:04.160 --> 00:06:05.080 align:middle line:90%
magazines.

00:06:05.080 --> 00:06:08.120 align:middle line:84%
>> He and I would work
in there during the day.

00:06:08.120 --> 00:06:10.630 align:middle line:84%
We would just have
the doors wide open.

00:06:10.630 --> 00:06:13.520 align:middle line:84%
And so people that lived in
the neighborhood would walk by.

00:06:13.520 --> 00:06:16.490 align:middle line:84%
And so they'd come in and
say, what are you doing?

00:06:16.490 --> 00:06:18.170 align:middle line:84%
And David would
say, you know, this

00:06:18.170 --> 00:06:20.840 align:middle line:84%
is the plan-- we're going
to make an art gallery here.

00:06:20.840 --> 00:06:22.730 align:middle line:84%
Enough people would
say, you know,

00:06:22.730 --> 00:06:24.260 align:middle line:84%
