01:00:12.200 --> 01:00:13.610 align:middle line:90%
it's going in.

01:00:13.610 --> 01:00:15.050 align:middle line:90%
The awakened state.

01:00:15.050 --> 01:00:17.180 align:middle line:90%
The mind's expansive.

01:00:17.180 --> 01:00:20.900 align:middle line:84%
But you've even seen yourself
perform in such a way because

01:00:20.900 --> 01:00:22.740 align:middle line:90%
of this state of presence.

01:00:22.740 --> 01:00:25.220 align:middle line:84%
So we all have had moments
in the zone, if that's

01:00:25.220 --> 01:00:26.930 align:middle line:90%
what you want to call it.

01:00:26.930 --> 01:00:30.770 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we're
seeking-- to live there,

01:00:30.770 --> 01:00:33.616 align:middle line:84%
to live in this awakened
state, this clarity.

01:00:33.616 --> 01:00:39.860 align:middle line:84%
Sit, let the noise
subside, and be at peace.

01:00:39.860 --> 01:00:43.850 align:middle line:90%
>> How is it that sitting--

01:00:43.850 --> 01:00:50.600 align:middle line:84%
not eating, not
talking, not reading,

01:00:50.600 --> 01:00:53.335 align:middle line:84%
but just that sort of
classical idea of meditation.

01:00:53.335 --> 01:00:54.650 align:middle line:90%
You're just sitting there.

01:00:54.650 --> 01:00:57.320 align:middle line:90%
You're not doing anything.

01:00:57.320 --> 01:01:00.892 align:middle line:84%
You're not even ruminating
on your thoughts.

01:01:00.892 --> 01:01:03.350 align:middle line:84%
>> Meditation is one of the
few things that I've found that

01:01:03.350 --> 01:01:07.550 align:middle line:84%
actually creates more time,
because we're actually slowing

01:01:07.550 --> 01:01:09.520 align:middle line:84%
down, realigning
with our breath,

01:01:09.520 --> 01:01:12.740 align:middle line:84%
moving the mind back into
a place of stillness,

01:01:12.740 --> 01:01:14.180 align:middle line:90%
connecting with our center.

01:01:14.180 --> 01:01:16.700 align:middle line:84%
It does this really
magical thing where

01:01:16.700 --> 01:01:21.170 align:middle line:84%
it starts to create more space,
and more time, and more peace,

01:01:21.170 --> 01:01:23.340 align:middle line:90%
and more grace, and more ease.

01:01:23.340 --> 01:01:25.670 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, it just
realigns everything.

01:01:25.670 --> 01:01:29.750 align:middle line:84%
It's like a big board meeting
of all the parts of your being

01:01:29.750 --> 01:01:31.380 align:middle line:90%
that get together and, OK.

01:01:31.380 --> 01:01:39.980 align:middle line:90%


01:01:39.980 --> 01:01:42.100 align:middle line:90%
>> Yoga means connecting to God.

01:01:42.100 --> 01:01:52.440 align:middle line:84%
The individual, Jiva, remembers
the divinity, cosmic awareness,

01:01:52.440 --> 01:01:53.850 align:middle line:90%
god.

01:01:53.850 --> 01:01:56.120 align:middle line:84%
What does standing on your
head have to do with that?

01:01:56.120 --> 01:01:58.660 align:middle line:84%
What does bending forward
have to do with that?

01:01:58.660 --> 01:02:00.190 align:middle line:84%
What does twisting
here, twisting

01:02:00.190 --> 01:02:03.230 align:middle line:90%
there have to do with that?

01:02:03.230 --> 01:02:08.980 align:middle line:84%
And so I feel very, very good
about offering the answers

01:02:08.980 --> 01:02:10.390 align:middle line:90%
to those questions.

01:02:10.390 --> 01:02:15.070 align:middle line:84%
You bring 100% of your
focus to what you're doing.

01:02:15.070 --> 01:02:18.740 align:middle line:84%
In my experience,
limited though it is,

01:02:18.740 --> 01:02:22.000 align:middle line:84%
I had never come across anybody
that explained any of that

01:02:22.000 --> 01:02:22.800 align:middle line:90%
to me.

01:02:22.800 --> 01:02:26.590 align:middle line:84%
Now, as you inhale, you're
going to shift forward

01:02:26.590 --> 01:02:27.964 align:middle line:90%
so your feet are pointed.

01:02:27.964 --> 01:02:29.380 align:middle line:84%
And you're going
to just lift up--

01:02:29.380 --> 01:02:30.920 align:middle line:90%
levitate your head, your leg up.

01:02:30.920 --> 01:02:37.890 align:middle line:84%
Specific Asanas have to
do with specific chakras.

01:02:37.890 --> 01:02:41.200 align:middle line:84%
And specific chakras
have to do with

01:02:41.200 --> 01:02:47.140 align:middle line:84%
specific karmic relationships
that we have with others.

01:02:47.140 --> 01:02:50.280 align:middle line:84%
When the Lord of Enlightenment
chases after them,

01:02:50.280 --> 01:02:56.410 align:middle line:84%
that Asana practice can actually
lead you directly to yoga,

01:02:56.410 --> 01:02:58.120 align:middle line:90%
to enlightenment.

01:02:58.120 --> 01:02:59.560 align:middle line:90%
How?

01:02:59.560 --> 01:03:04.420 align:middle line:84%
By assisting you in resolving
the karmic relationships

01:03:04.420 --> 01:03:07.300 align:middle line:84%
that you have with
others, which are really

01:03:07.300 --> 01:03:11.913 align:middle line:84%
creating the obstacles
between you and God.

01:03:11.913 --> 01:03:14.871 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:03:14.871 --> 01:03:22.270 align:middle line:90%


01:03:22.270 --> 01:03:26.010 align:middle line:84%
>> There's the step in the
class, when you take a class.

01:03:26.010 --> 01:03:28.290 align:middle line:10%
And even though you don't
know anything about it,

01:03:28.290 --> 01:03:29.580 align:middle line:10%
you just feel it.

01:03:29.580 --> 01:03:32.984 align:middle line:10%
The chanting, the Asanas,
the breathing-- everything's

01:03:32.984 --> 01:03:34.224 align:middle line:10%
so beautiful.

01:03:34.224 --> 01:03:39.190 align:middle line:90%


01:03:39.190 --> 01:03:42.567 align:middle line:84%
And I think people are looking
for something like this,

01:03:42.567 --> 01:03:46.110 align:middle line:84%
like some deeper
meaning to life.

01:03:46.110 --> 01:03:47.580 align:middle line:90%
And I found that in yoga.

01:03:47.580 --> 01:03:50.520 align:middle line:90%


01:03:50.520 --> 01:03:55.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Yoga brings reverence for
life that we can't feel when

01:03:55.710 --> 01:04:00.240 align:middle line:84%
we're so strained because
we have so much tension

01:04:00.240 --> 01:04:01.220 align:middle line:90%
in our mind.

01:04:01.220 --> 01:04:02.470 align:middle line:90%
You're in the present moment.

01:04:02.470 --> 01:04:05.070 align:middle line:84%
It's not like we're
following these rules--

01:04:05.070 --> 01:04:07.600 align:middle line:90%
oh, you know, it's so terrible.

01:04:07.600 --> 01:04:12.900 align:middle line:84%
I have to practice nonviolence,
and I have to always be kind,

01:04:12.900 --> 01:04:15.400 align:middle line:84%
and I have to always
think about others first.

01:04:15.400 --> 01:04:23.870 align:middle line:84%
And oh, you know, like this
severe life of sacrifice.

01:04:23.870 --> 01:04:27.780 align:middle line:90%


01:04:27.780 --> 01:04:32.580 align:middle line:84%
They've helped countless people
realize where happiness really

01:04:32.580 --> 01:04:35.240 align:middle line:90%
comes from.

01:04:35.240 --> 01:04:38.420 align:middle line:84%
>> It is a way to
connect with yourself.

01:04:38.420 --> 01:04:41.840 align:middle line:84%
We're so busy out there in the
blah, blah, blah, blah, blah,

01:04:41.840 --> 01:04:43.370 align:middle line:90%
blah, blah.

01:04:43.370 --> 01:04:47.300 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of the day,
we only have ourselves.

01:04:47.300 --> 01:04:51.260 align:middle line:84%
I find that doing my practice
and then going into meditation

01:04:51.260 --> 01:04:53.540 align:middle line:90%
is a totality in completion.

01:04:53.540 --> 01:04:55.610 align:middle line:84%
>> And it attracts you,
and it pulls you in.

01:04:55.610 --> 01:04:58.250 align:middle line:84%
And you think, oh, I
want to feel that more.

01:04:58.250 --> 01:05:00.590 align:middle line:84%
And that's why you go
deeper and deeper into it,

01:05:00.590 --> 01:05:03.320 align:middle line:84%
because you just want to be able
to feel like that all the time.

01:05:03.320 --> 01:05:06.770 align:middle line:84%
Chant, and you meditate, and
you do the Asana practice

01:05:06.770 --> 01:05:08.930 align:middle line:90%
because you get glimpses of it.

01:05:08.930 --> 01:05:10.430 align:middle line:10%
>> It's a practice
of enlightenment.

01:05:10.430 --> 01:05:15.110 align:middle line:10%
It's a practice of really
tapping into what's real.

01:05:15.110 --> 01:05:19.870 align:middle line:84%
>> I used to think,
oh, that's so lofty--

01:05:19.870 --> 01:05:24.380 align:middle line:84%
enlightenment, compassion
for all beings.

01:05:24.380 --> 01:05:28.480 align:middle line:84%
Why can't we tone it
down a little bit?

01:05:28.480 --> 01:05:30.860 align:middle line:84%
You know, make it maybe a
little bit more accessible.

01:05:30.860 --> 01:05:36.540 align:middle line:84%
But as the years have passed,
now I think, well, gosh,

01:05:36.540 --> 01:05:37.340 align:middle line:90%
why not?

01:05:37.340 --> 01:05:40.760 align:middle line:84%
Yoga is to get enlightened,
so why skip that part?

01:05:40.760 --> 01:05:45.450 align:middle line:90%


01:05:45.450 --> 01:05:51.200 align:middle line:84%
>> You've got three time periods
of Jivamukti history, I guess.

01:05:51.200 --> 01:05:55.510 align:middle line:84%
Chapter one, David Life and
Sharon Gannon, their teachers,

01:05:55.510 --> 01:05:56.610 align:middle line:90%
and their practice.

01:05:56.610 --> 01:06:01.440 align:middle line:84%
Chapter two, the New York
school in the East Village,

01:06:01.440 --> 01:06:03.900 align:middle line:84%
in Union Square and
the teacher trainings.

01:06:03.900 --> 01:06:08.910 align:middle line:90%
And chapter three, Jules Febre.

01:06:08.910 --> 01:06:13.140 align:middle line:84%
>> David wanted to teach yoga
to kids, so he borrowed Jules.

01:06:13.140 --> 01:06:16.440 align:middle line:84%
>> I think the very first yoga
classes that I taught Jules is

01:06:16.440 --> 01:06:17.820 align:middle line:90%
when he was four years old.

01:06:17.820 --> 01:06:20.350 align:middle line:84%
>> At some point,
Jules said to me,

01:06:20.350 --> 01:06:26.055 align:middle line:84%
do you think Uncle David would
take me with him to India?

01:06:26.055 --> 01:06:28.530 align:middle line:90%
>> So I took him to India.

01:06:28.530 --> 01:06:31.410 align:middle line:84%
And we took yoga
classes in Mysore

01:06:31.410 --> 01:06:33.540 align:middle line:90%
at 4:00 AM in the morning.

01:06:33.540 --> 01:06:36.630 align:middle line:84%
When he came back, he
said, OK, he did yoga.

01:06:36.630 --> 01:06:38.050 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

01:06:38.050 --> 01:06:38.850 align:middle line:90%
Finished.

01:06:38.850 --> 01:06:41.250 align:middle line:90%
>> He was done with yoga.

01:06:41.250 --> 01:06:43.200 align:middle line:84%
He didn't want
anything to do with it.

01:06:43.200 --> 01:06:46.330 align:middle line:10%
>> When I came to know him,
he wasn't doing anything.

01:06:46.330 --> 01:06:49.450 align:middle line:10%
So he was just hanging out,
getting into a little trouble.

01:06:49.450 --> 01:06:52.480 align:middle line:84%
>> He just fell in with some
kids that took it to the next

01:06:52.480 --> 01:06:53.280 align:middle line:90%
level.

01:06:53.280 --> 01:06:56.010 align:middle line:84%
Teenagers, they don't
realize the seriousness

01:06:56.010 --> 01:06:58.440 align:middle line:90%
of their actions sometimes.

01:06:58.440 --> 01:07:01.230 align:middle line:10%
So he got arrested.

01:07:01.230 --> 01:07:02.850 align:middle line:10%
>> I was sitting
in a prison cell,

01:07:02.850 --> 01:07:05.470 align:middle line:10%
thinking about a chant that
we do a lot at Jivamukti--

01:07:05.470 --> 01:07:06.690 align:middle line:10%
make me an instrument.

01:07:06.690 --> 01:07:08.460 align:middle line:84%
And I wasn't doing
it consciously.

01:07:08.460 --> 01:07:12.390 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't like, and now
I will do my mantra.

01:07:12.390 --> 01:07:16.560 align:middle line:84%
>> All of a sudden, all those
early introductions started

01:07:16.560 --> 01:07:17.700 align:middle line:90%
to kick in.

01:07:17.700 --> 01:07:21.510 align:middle line:84%
And he became the yogi
he is and the great yoga

01:07:21.510 --> 01:07:23.040 align:middle line:90%
teacher that he is.

01:07:23.040 --> 01:07:27.000 align:middle line:84%
It's just-- have been an
amazing transformation.

01:07:27.000 --> 01:07:30.030 align:middle line:84%
>> What we seen, what
we surround ourselves,

01:07:30.030 --> 01:07:31.530 align:middle line:90%
we're influenced by.

01:07:31.530 --> 01:07:32.730 align:middle line:90%
And that changes us.

01:07:32.730 --> 01:07:35.000 align:middle line:84%
And if what we are
surrounding ourselves

01:07:35.000 --> 01:07:39.230 align:middle line:84%
is with things that
bring us to know more,

01:07:39.230 --> 01:07:41.610 align:middle line:84%
to understand more,
to connect more--

01:07:41.610 --> 01:07:44.160 align:middle line:84%
and then we might be
ready for something else.

01:07:44.160 --> 01:07:47.250 align:middle line:84%
>> We invited Jules to Cape Town
to share some of his teachings

01:07:47.250 --> 01:07:50.310 align:middle line:84%
with our students and a group
of dynamic children from

01:07:50.310 --> 01:07:52.805 align:middle line:84%
an informal settlement
called Khayelitsha,

01:07:52.805 --> 01:07:56.980 align:middle line:84%
who are being taught mindfulness
and positive upliftment

01:07:56.980 --> 01:07:58.786 align:middle line:90%
by the Earthchild Project.

01:07:58.786 --> 01:08:02.258 align:middle line:90%
>> [SINGING]

01:08:02.258 --> 01:08:10.194 align:middle line:90%


01:08:10.194 --> 01:08:14.190 align:middle line:84%
>> There is an incredible amount
of suffering in this world,

01:08:14.190 --> 01:08:15.556 align:middle line:90%
and it's vast.

01:08:15.556 --> 01:08:17.305 align:middle line:84%
And especially when
it's happening to you,

01:08:17.305 --> 01:08:19.429 align:middle line:84%
it's like, oh, the suffering
couldn't be any worse.

01:08:19.429 --> 01:08:22.458 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:08:22.458 --> 01:08:26.895 align:middle line:90%


01:08:26.895 --> 01:08:29.819 align:middle line:84%
But on the one hand, the
suffering is immense.

01:08:29.819 --> 01:08:34.170 align:middle line:84%
And on the other hand, it's
that hand that pulls you out

01:08:34.170 --> 01:08:37.430 align:middle line:90%
of stagnation.

01:08:37.430 --> 01:08:42.210 align:middle line:84%
It's usually the tipping point
for people, that suffering,

01:08:42.210 --> 01:08:46.771 align:middle line:84%
that allows them to
connect to others.

01:08:46.771 --> 01:08:49.700 align:middle line:90%
[INAUDIBLE]

01:08:49.700 --> 01:08:52.109 align:middle line:84%
I found that the best
thing that I can do

01:08:52.109 --> 01:08:57.032 align:middle line:84%
is live as beautifully
as possible.

01:08:57.032 --> 01:09:00.448 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:09:00.448 --> 01:09:04.970 align:middle line:90%


01:09:04.970 --> 01:09:07.654 align:middle line:84%
>> I see Jivamukti being
